          "body": "The fifth move (11:28-32) integrates Gentile and Jewish histories into a single pattern of mercy. Israel is currently 'enemies' from the gospel standpoint but 'beloved' from the election standpoint, because the gifts and calling of God are *irrevocable* (*ametameletos*, 11:29). The key verb is *eleeo* — to show mercy. Gentiles were once disobedient, now have been shown mercy because of Israel's disobedience; Israel is now disobedient so that mercy may come to them through the mercy shown to Gentiles (11:30-31). The summation in v. 32 is staggering: *God has shut up all in disobedience so that He may show mercy to all.* The 'all' here is corporate-historical, not universalist — both groups (Jew and Gentile) share the same diagnosis (disobedience) and the same hope (mercy)."
